2026-02-13 (v1.07)
- The positional argument for input files now recognizes .tka
  in addition to .jac and .jca.
- The optional --all argument now also recognizes .tka
  in addition to .jac and .jca. All extensions are handled case-insensitively.
- The program removes residual \r characters that may result from CRLF line
  endings on macOS or Linux.

2023-12-10 (v1.06)
- The headings of .csv and .xlsx output files are now written to a single line
  by default, and can be divided into name headings and unit (sub)headings
  via a command-line argument.
- The starting cell of an .xlsx output file can now be designated
  via a command-line argument.

2023-12-06 (v1.05)
- The default encoding of a .jac/.jca file has been changed to
  cp932 (Shift JIS).
- The fourth noncount record of a .jac/.jca file, or a comment in its
  corresponding binary file, can now be parsed correctly and is mirrored
  on the resulting output .dat file.
- The y/n selection prompt can now be toggled off via a command-line argument.

2020-07-18 (v1.04)
- The directory structure has been reorganized.
- .jac/.jca files can now be designated with their relative or absolute paths
  included.
- The names of the command-line arguments 'dat_<..>' have been changed to
  'out_<..>', but can still be used.
- .jac/.jca files containing blank lines can now be parsed without errors.
- The prepending and appending flags of output filenames can be designated
  via the command-line options.
- .jca files can now be processed in addition to .jac files.

2019-04-20 (v1.03)
- A randomized .jac sample file has been included in the program release.

2019-04-08 (v1.02)
- Detection efficiencies can now be input manually.

2019-04-07 (v1.01)
- Source code reorganized
- Conversion formulas can now be specified via an input file.

2019-02-04 (v1.00)
- jac2dat.pl first written
